<br>
What makes Furor (from FoH) better than that other 60war that didn't make it into FoH?<br>
<br>
Assuming you have two warriors, both the same level, exact same equip, same race, same hp, same ac, same atk, same skills (1hs, Taunt, Swimming, etc.) would would put warriorA over the edge? What would warriorA have to know to make him a better warrior?<br>
<br>
The reason I ask is because, quite frankly, I'm tired (as a Half Elf) of being passed up for a &quot;better&quot; warrior simply because they have a bit better gear or are a Ogre or something. Or because the Ogre has the cliche warrior armor: full crusty, 2 lammies, 65hp ring, CC ears, he must be better because everyone else has seen that stuff before (whereas I have a mix of stuff, only 2 pcs of crusty left [and I'm about to replace the arms, leaving only the legs]) So I can't be as good of a warr because I have all this crazy armor that people have never heard of.<br>
<br>
Your level and equipment is a big part of how good you are, but if you are close in those respects, SOMETHING has to make one warrior better than the other - what is that SOMETHING?<br>
<br>
I know if there is me vs. a level 46 war w/ fungi, full planar/thurg armor, 10/18 and a frosty, 8th coldain ring, djarns ring, etc. he's going to take my spot whereever we go no matter how EBAY'ed he is (which brings up another point, how do I convince people that I'm better than Ebayed_n00b_01 even though his equipment is leagues ahead of mine?)<br>
<br>
I've been reading this boards for awhile and I've learned alot, and they are helping me learn new and good things that have helped me alot. And I want to make myself the absolute best warrior I can be, whenever I put the LFG tag on, I want people to be fighting over which group I should go to, I want my rep to be a legendary one. <br>
<br>
&quot;Oh Baadan! He's the guy who saved that &lt;insert zone here&gt; raid last month! Man if it was for that &lt;thing&gt; he did, the whole raid would've wiped!!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Get Baadan! Screw that 50warrior he's @#%$ to Baadan, man that kid has some l337 skeelz!&quot;<br>
<br>
blah blah you know what I mean, kinda like walking around and seeing a very well-respected person on your server (leader of resident uber guild or something) you know if that person goes LFG, people are going to kill to get him, simply because his grasp of the game is so in-depth, nothing goes wrong when he is around.<br>
<br>
