Kane Bayle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uraunstoncutter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RaunStoncutter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/17/02 8:21:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=950.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://raunstonecutter.freehomepage.com/bunnyhop.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_atk.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What Makes A Good Warrior?</span><hr size=1> What will make you the best warrior will be how well you know the game.  Be aware of things like warping points, mobs abilities, spells, drops, locations, quests, etc.  While this may seem like a ton of knowledge, this will help you with any other EQ character you play.<br>
<br>
Most people who have never played a warrior or who don't respect warriors think all we have to do is mash auto attack and hit taunt every time it refreshes.  I think we all know there's simply more to our class than just hitting things.  Every class should learn these things, but many just forget about it and concentrate on getting that uber stuff.  <br>
<br>
A warrior's primairy goal is agro control, and second is hit points.  Agro control is the most useful thing you can learn, and will make you well known and respected in the higher end portion of the game.  One thing you should know is to trust your taunt, and not rely on the taunt key.  Yes, max the skill, but don't hit it every time it refreshes.  Save it for when the shaman slow's and the enchanter tashes.<br>
<br>
Your Hp/AC are a direct result of your equipement.  With that in mind, you need to save as much money as you can to keep your equipement up.  Now you probably won't beable to buy everything you want (SBoZ HoH please Santa!), but you should try your best to make sure you use your money to keep your equipement up.  Things like getting haste, 6/65 rings, some basic resist gear, decent weapons, ect, are all things you should put your money into.  You do what ever you can to get as much agro, HP and AC as you can.  The more of those you have, the better a warrior you can be.  Will you be able to keep up with ebayers?  Probably not, but you can do just as well after they die, and pick up their slack.<br>
<br>
The road to being a good warrior is a hard one, espically since we all had to deal with the twinks out there who at lvl 5 had CoF's and CBoL's.  But the lessions you learn about the game from not being power leveled will help you greatly in this way.  Also, keep an eye on the ebayers as they will teach you the wrong way to do thing and save you the death learning from their mistakes. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31658">Raun Stonecutter 55 Warrior</a>
