<br>
<a href="http://www.prexus.com">Prexus server</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukimagure.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kimagure</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/17/02 11:15:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=950.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_atk.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What Makes A Good Warrior?</span><hr size=1> Like people have said above, gear aside, the one thing that will make you shine is your knowledge and feel for the game.  As a warrior you can end up being the puller for the party many times, more so at lower levels because you can survive longer taking hits and make it back to the group alive.  In this regard you learn about mobs, spawns, tricks and tactics.  <br>
<br>
Also there are little things you can do that make you stand out.  For example, do you have a magic shield?  Since only big races get slam and kick doesnt have a stun component until level 55, learning to ghetto bash caster mobs is a big plus to many people.  Bash is a stun and interrupting casters is always a nice thing especially those pesky cleric mobs.  Back in the 40s and early 50s people seemed pleasantly surprised when I would swap in a shield and bash-interrupt mobs.<br>
<br>
Other little things I can think of:<br>
<br>
- Multiple &quot;incoming&quot; messages letting the group you have 1 or multiple mobs coming and if possible able to quickly point out which mob you'll be on to give the CC person a heads up on which to target for mez or root.<br>
<br>
- Have an assist button and always use it if you're not the main tank<br>
<br>
- Be aware of mob positioning.  Are you pushing the mob in a bad direction?  Is the mob's back open for rogue backstabs?  Especially at raids, you'll see everyone but the main tank hitting the mob from behind.  This means of course the mob is being pushed at you.  Therefore, you can direct the mob where you want him to go by having your back face that direction.<br>
<br>
- Use the F9 key to be aware of your surroundings when needed.<br>
<br>
- Save the taunt key for moments when you lose aggro, not just hit it as soon as it pops up everytime.<br>
<br>
- Later on when you get disciplines, have a feel for when you think you should use it and dont be afraid to use it if you deem necessary.<br>
<br>
- Sometimes sacrifice is necessary.  What's more important, that you make it to zone when there's a train or the cleric that's gonna be able to rez you and everyone else make it safely?  Or if you're pulling and you know you have too many mobs on you and you cant zone, just die rather than bring them all to group and wipe them out too.<br>
<br>
- Crystalized Pumice Stone is your friend.  In certain situations, pulling with one you can do some fun stuff. e.g. Seb Crypt<br>
<br>
- Have a personality.  Sometimes, the best conversations come from random people you meet while exp'ing and sometimes groups lead to friendships.<br>
<br>
Reputations are made over time and it's mostly by your grouping experiences.  There are people I still remember from leveling in my 40s and 50s whether it was good or bad.  In certain zones like for example Overthere, Lower Guk and Karnor's you can group with the same people multiple times.  While I dont think you'll ever have a legendary reputation, one good grouping experience may go a long way later on down the road. <p><Table Style='Filter: Alpha(Opacity=100, FinishOpacity=50, Style=2, StartX=85, FinishX=20, StartY=0, FinishY=0)'><B><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6495" target="magelo"><Font Color=#FFCC33 Size=3 Face=Times New Roman, Helvetica>Rula - warh0bbit, esq.</Font></a><br><a href="http://www.shattered-sorcery.com/blight/" target="Blight"><Font Color=CC00FF><i>&#60Blight&#62, Vazaelle</i></Font></a><br></B></Table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uroehm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Roehm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will KICK YOUR @$$</span><br>  Posts: 471<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/17/02 11:56:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=950.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_atk.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What Makes A Good Warrior?</span><hr size=1> To sum up all the long posts above...<br>
